text: My stay at Thor and Agnieszka’s house was definitely a pleasure. They are very hospitable, friendly and openminded couple.  Lots of travelling experience. Very nice and clean house with a Polish cat -Euro. 😊  I really enjoy sitting together and talking on the couch, exchanging our experiences and views on different things, laughs, jokes etc. Thor even knows the company I am working for in Randers - small world. :P  It was a pity I arrived a bit late the evening before and we all had early plans for the next day. Would really like to spend more time together. Many thanks to Thor and Agnieszka.

I stayed with Thor and Agnieszka during my biking trip across Denmark. They welcomed me and my sweaty clothes in a day earlier than originally planned and were very hospitable. Thor made some soup for all of us for dinner and we completed a puzzle while mostly talking about the travel that each of us have done. They have a great sense of humor and are quite ambitious; Thor says he wants to visit 100 countries by the time he's 50! Overall it was a great experience and I highly recommend them as hosts

text:
Thor and Agnieszka have a beautiful home in Randers with an amazing garden. It makes up a in the middle of nature scenery while being in a city. In this setting they served us a rich and delicious BBQ. Also they are super fun to hang out, they've visited so many countries and have so many stories to tell. The finish makes their cute but a little crazy cat Euro and Thors super dark humour.

And if you ever want to change the fact that you never stayed in switzerland let us know.

It was an absolute pleasure to stay with Thor and Agnieszka 😊 they are very friendly and hospitable people! They showed me around their beautiful city (and bars Haha) and we went out to see an old castle ruin! I hope I can return their kindness and hospitality when I move to Hirtshals 😊

I decided to move to Randers, so I found Thor and Agnieszka through CS to be in their home in my first days in Randers before I moved to my own apartment. Their home is so clean, warm (I was there at winter) and comfortable. On the first night, Thor just came back from work to home when I arrived, however, he got ready to go with me to the train station to pick an another couchsurfer ( my future roommate, Hossein). Agnieszka cooked delicious meatballs with roasted vegetables and salad. She guided us with a map to explore some attractions in Randers center. In the second day, after having a breakfast, we went to the city center by Thor's car and in the afternoon he picked us up to back home. At night we tried to cook an Iranian food with rice and Shirazi Salad. I hope they liked it:)
After the dinner we talked about social subjects and also we shared our experiences about our previous trips.

I am glad that now we are living in the same city! Thor and Agnieszka you are so welcome to come to our home. We can provide another Iranian food for you;)

To sum up, Thor and Agnieszka are very honest and reliable. They are so hospitable. I recommend them 100%.

Thor - the big Danish friend with a big Danish sense of humour:) He took me and my friends to many places in Denmark, we were betting even on horse races, visited "Graceland" in Randers and we were eating sausages in some strange park with animals and many kids:) The same as me he likes metal music!

Together with my friend Dorothea I had a great stay at Henriettes house. She accepted us even if it was really last-minute and she welcomed us with open arms. She even cooked a great typical Danish dinner in vegan style when we arrived. Also she gave us many great tips for our trip through Denmark. Before we left we got a tasty breakfast and we would love to stay with her again in the future as she really is a caring and amazing host.

Henriette was an awesome host! She was super spontaneous regarding my request to stay and even cooked for me amazingly good tasting vegan dinner. I loved the way she senses her environment and tries to be a good person where ever she could. Staying at her place felt like staying over night at a person you know for years. I wish her a lot of sunny days this summer and hope that she will manage to do her Europe tour. I would not hesitate to visit her again! :)

I actually first talked to Henriette a while back. We met on a couchsurfing group dedicated to Geocachers.  So I have to start by saying that we have this in common. If you, the reader of this reference, have no idea what GEOCACHING is, feel free to ask either one of us :D

Back to the matter at hand! We did not manage to meet when I had my event in Aarhus this February, but then the news came that I can attend the MEGA Event in Randers (GC63TQP) so my first thought was, of course to contact Henriette and see if maybe she can host me and my girlfriend during the event.

She was very kind to offer us a place to sleep for both days, but unfortunately we could only spend one night here. Because of work, we could only come to Randers on Saturday, not Friday evening for the pre-event :( . 

After a lovely day during the MEGA event and a tasty grill dinner we went home. Thanks again Henriette for also offering us a ride :D It is so much better to have the same schedule as the host / guest so you can spend more time together.  Although we were all tired and we knew we had to wake up early to get to the second event (CITO), we stayed late in the night for more socializing, TB logging, and other fun conversations and story telling. 

It was a perfect evening after a perfect day! Oh, and the dogs were awesome! 

Very cozy house and really awesome host! I definitely would like to visit her again. Oh and did I mention that we slept in a room upstairs? I love attics!!!

Thank you very much!

I stayed with Henriette for 2 night and it was such a nice time! We have similar intrests so it was really nice to talk with her and hear her hiking, cycling and travelling stories. We went for some walks and she reminded me how cool is geocaching! Also in the kitchen Henriette is good, so food always were really delicious! She helped me a lot with some things and advices also for my trip. I feel really lucky that I had a chance to stay with her, Clara and both lovely dogs! Thank you so much for everything!! :)

Henriette generously offered to host me for a night when I was passing by on my bike tour.  She offered dinner and took me and  her other guest to  see a  a fabulous monastery nearby.  Only downside was that she introduced me to what may well  turn out my new addiction: Geo caching , which seems like a funhobby(that I don't really have the time for) ;)  She's a really cool woman with a lovely home!  All my recommendations!

Henriette is absolutley amazing! Even though we arrived much later than we expected she was patient and came to pick us up in Hald. From there on the hospitality just continued! She made us feel like we were home, we got food, beds, towels and even a long ride towards our next destination the day after! An amazing woman with a big heart for people and two amazing dogs. I warmly recommend getting hosted by her if you are passing by. Peace!
I am sure Henriette is very polite and hospitable person. I didn't have enough time to visit personally, but I'll do it at the first opportunity next time when i'll be in Denmark

Henriette is a very easy-going companion and good host. With a lot of understanding, as usual with people who went through hard times in life. 
Very helpful, excellent cook! 
(But beware - the dogs know it, so they are also adapted to vegetarian food - ready to snatch it from your plate :)
The place is not in Randers town, but a small settlement called Mellerup (so guests who do not come in their own vehicle are generally dependent on Henriette having time to pick them up)
Both her and her teenage daughter Klara would clearly be very pleasant and undemanding guests!

It was nice from Peter to host us, although we are Germans ;) 
so from that you know that he is quite tolerant.
The stay at yours was fun, we enjoyed hanging out with a nerd, who exploits Germany for it's alcohol.
Thanks to you we finally had our european road trip hehe..

So if you're into beer, muesli and power-protein-food, you totally should stay at Peters!

You were the perfect host, thanks for showing us around in Aarhus and the countryside!
We will come back when there are open shops and students hanging out, we actually have to come back anyway to graduate in Denmark ;)
We would offer you to stay at our place in Germany, but as we know how much you love this country, we won't do that!
Thanks again for the good times,
Alice & Marie

text: My boyfriend and I were last minute with our bookings, we called Birgitte only 4 hours before and she still welcomed us with pleasure! The house is a little far from Viborg but the location was perfect for a get away time in the country side to get some time to relax. It was the highlight of our trip. We met Birgitte, her partner Mads and the son Anders. They were really generous, we exchanged a lot on different subjects and shared many memories with them. We felt like part of the family<3. Thank you very much!

After 5 hours of driving, me and my mom reached Signe's place in Randers. She was waiting us to have a delicious dinner she cooked us for. After it we talked and we shared lots of information about our lives, traveling and Denmark. Also the places she recommend us around Randers and Aarhus were really nice.  She was really friendly and nice person to stay with! We made breakfast together and it couldn't be better. Also she showed us her pottery studio and showed me and my mom how to do it. It was a really cool learning experience!! We had so much fun and learnt lots of new stuff about Danish Culture and lifestyle; and of course we won a friend. I will recommend staying with Signe 200% :) 

We will look forward to meet you in Gran Canaria!
